Implemented the minimal fix.

Changed JSON Pointer traversal so that when a syntactically valid pointer continues past a scalar value, it returns `NO_SUCH_FIELD` instead of `INVALID_JSON_POINTER`, while malformed pointers still return `INVALID_JSON_POINTER`.

Updated:
- `include/simdjson/generic/ondemand/document-inl.h`
- `include/simdjson/generic/ondemand/value-inl.h`
- `include/simdjson/dom/element-inl.h`
- `singleheader/simdjson.h`

Verified with small DOM and On Demand compile/run checks for:
- `/document/key4/sub` → `NO_SUCH_FIELD`
- `document/key4/sub` → `INVALID_JSON_POINTER`
- `/document/key4/~2` → `INVALID_JSON_POINTER`
